text.section:
A person may be found by the sentencing judge to have committed an offense specified below as a result of a hate crime if the person intentionally because of race, color, religion, sexual orientation, or national origin of another individual or group of individuals violates a provision of any one (1) of the following:
KRS 508.010, 508.020, 508.025, or 508.030;
KRS 508.050 or 508.060;
KRS 508.100 or 508.110;
KRS 509.020;
KRS 510.040, 510.050, 510.060, 510.070, 510.080, 510.090, 510.100, or 510.110;
KRS 512.020, 512.050, or 512.060;
KRS 513.020, 513.030, or 513.040; or
KRS 525.020, 525.050, 525.060, 525.070, or 525.080.
